# IslamWiki Release Notes - Version 0.0.35

**Release Date:** August 2, 2025  
**Previous Version:** 0.0.34  
**Next Version:** 0.0.36

## 🎉 Major Features

### ✅ User Authentication & Profile System
- **Complete User Authentication**: Full login/logout functionality with session management
- **User Profile Pages**: Private and public profile viewing with user statistics
- **User Dropdown Menu**: ZamZam.js-powered dropdown with Dashboard, Profile, Settings, and Logout links
- **Session Management**: Proper session handling with secure configuration

### ✅ Navigation & UI Improvements
- **Search Bar**: Added comprehensive search functionality to top navigation
- **User Navigation**: Restored user dropdown menu with proper authentication state
- **Responsive Design**: Mobile-friendly navigation with proper breakpoints
- **ZamZam.js Integration**: Maintained custom framework integration for interactivity

### ✅ Project Organization
- **Test File Organization**: Moved all test files from `public/` to `tests/web/` (73 files)
- **Debug File Organization**: Moved all debug files from `public/` to `debug/` (20 files)
- **Clean Public Directory**: Removed development files from web-accessible directory
- **Proper Structure**: Follows web application best practices

## 🔧 Technical Improvements

### ✅ Dependency Injection & Service Providers
- **SkinServiceProvider**: Properly registered skin management system
- **Settings Binding**: Added comprehensive settings configuration for all services
- **Application Container**: Unified container management across the application
- **Service Registration**: All service providers properly registered and booted

### ✅ Authentication System
- **AuthManager Integration**: Complete authentication system with database integration
- **Session Security**: Secure session handling with proper configuration
- **User Management**: Full user CRUD operations with proper validation
- **Admin User**: Default admin user (admin/password) for system access

### ✅ Error Handling & Debugging
- **Comprehensive Error Handling**: Proper error pages and logging
- **Debug Tools**: Organized debug scripts in dedicated directory
- **Development Tools**: Test scripts properly organized and accessible
- **Logging System**: Structured logging with proper configuration

## 🐛 Bug Fixes

### ✅ Critical Fixes
- **Profile Page Error**: Fixed "No binding found for [skin.manager]" error
- **Settings Binding**: Resolved missing settings binding for LoggingServiceProvider
- **Session Issues**: Fixed session regeneration warnings
- **Container Conflicts**: Resolved dependency injection container conflicts

### ✅ Navigation Fixes
- **User Dropdown**: Fixed missing user dropdown for authenticated users
- **Authentication State**: Proper detection and display of user login status
- **Search Bar**: Restored search functionality to top navigation
- **Responsive Issues**: Fixed mobile navigation display issues

## 📁 File Organization

### ✅ Moved Files
- **Test Files**: `public/test-*.php` → `tests/web/test-*.php` (73 files)
- **Debug Files**: `public/debug-*.php` → `debug/debug-*.php` (20 files)
- **Test Directory**: `public/tests/` → `tests/web/` (consolidated)
- **Debug Directory**: `public/debug/` → `debug/` (consolidated)

### ✅ Updated Files
- **public/index.php**: Main application entry point with proper service registration
- **src/Core/Application.php**: Added settings binding for service providers
- **src/Http/Controllers/ProfileController.php**: Fixed authentication integration
- **.gitignore**: Updated to reflect new file organization

## 🔒 Security Improvements

### ✅ Authentication Security
- **Session Security**: Proper session configuration with secure settings
- **Password Hashing**: Secure password hashing with bcrypt
- **CSRF Protection**: CSRF token implementation for forms
- **Input Validation**: Proper input validation and sanitization

### ✅ File Organization Security
- **Development Files**: Moved development files out of web-accessible directory
- **Test Files**: Organized test files in dedicated directory
- **Debug Files**: Organized debug files in dedicated directory
- **Public Directory**: Clean public directory with only web-accessible files

